'''Al-Kuz''' is an [[impact crater]] on the anti-Saturn hemisphere of [[Saturn]]'s moon [[Enceladus (moon)|Enceladus]].  Al-Kuz was first observed in ''[[Cassini-Huygens Mission|Cassini]]'' images during that mission's March 2005 flyby of Enceladus.  It is located at 18.7° South [[Latitude]], 178.2° West [[Longitude]], and is 9.3 kilometers across.<ref name=gpn />  Since the crater's formation, numerous southwest-northeast trending fractures cut across the crater, forming canyons several hundred meters deep along the crater's rim.  In addition, a smaller impact occurred along the northern crater wall, forming a crater 4 kilometers wide.

Al-Kuz is named after one of the barber's six brothers in "[[The Hunchback's Tale]]" in ''[[The Book of One Thousand and One Nights]]''.

