{{BLP sources|date=October 2014}} {{Infobox astronaut | name = Anna Yuryevna Kikina | image = Anna Kikina 2013.jpg | image_size = | caption = | type = | nationality = Russian | status = Active | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|08|27|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Novosibirsk]], Russia | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Test cosmonaut | current_occupation = Engineer | previous_occupation = | rank = | space_time = | selection = [[List of astronauts by selection#2012|TsPK-16 Cosmonaut Group]] | missions = | insignia = | evas = | eva_time = | retirement = | awards = }}
'''Anna Yuryevna Kikina''' (born 27 August 1984 in [[Novosibirsk]]) is a Russian engineer and test cosmonaut, selected in 2012.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.themoscowtimes.com/business/article/russia-s-2nd-post-soviet-female-cosmonaut-in-line-for-space-station-mission/506383.html |title=Russia's 2nd Post-Soviet Female Cosmonaut in Line for Space Station Mission |publisher=themoscowtimes.com |date=3 September 2014}}</ref>
==Education== Kikina graduated with honors from the Novosibirsk State Academy of Water transport.
