{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | color = violet | name = ''Maripa virus'' | virus_group = v | ordo = ''[[Bunyavirales]]'' | familia = ''[[Hantaviridae]]'' | genus = ''[[Orthohantavirus]]'' | species = '''''Maripa virus''''' }}
'''Maripa virus''' is a single-stranded, enveloped, negative-sense RNA hantavirus species in the [[Bunyavirales]] order. It is a new variant strain of Rio Mamore virus. It was first isolated from a patient with hantavirus pulmonary syndrome in French Guiana.<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Matheus S, Lavergne A, de Thoisy B, Dussart P, Lacoste V |title=Complete genome sequence of a novel hantavirus variant of Rio Mamoré virus, Maripa virus, from French Guiana |journal=J. Virol. |volume=86 |issue=9 |pages=5399 |year=2012 |pmid=22492924 |pmc=3347398 |doi=10.1128/JVI.00337-12 |url=http://jvi.asm.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=22492924}}</ref>
== See also == *[[Rio Mamore virus]] *[[1993 Four Corners hantavirus outbreak]] *[[Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome]]
